cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for vision-based object tracking, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel network architecture that combines a deep convolutional neural network with a Bayesian loss layer, which involves ML techniques such as deep learning and probabilistic modeling. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on a standard tracking benchmark, which involves multimedia (MM) and robotics (RO) applications. Therefore, cs.MM and cs.RO are also likely categories.
